          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Direct measurement of  the  reaction  cross  section.",
                " After  the  etching of the mica foils detector,  the",
                " identification and counting  of  fission  fragments,",
                " and track analysis were carried out by using optical",
                " microscopes.  The emulsions were processed using the",
                " special  technique  to  obtain  very legible fission",
                " tracks in spite of background from alphaparticles."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors are presented."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photofission cross section of  U-238  induced  by",
                " monocromatic and polarized photons has been measured",
                " using the ladon facility.  The experiment  has  been",
                " performed  at six different energies in the range 46",
                " - 72 MeV by detecting the fission  fragments  either",
                " in  uranium-loaded  nuclear-track emulsion plates or",
                " in uranium-mica sandwiches.  During  the  experiment",
                " the  main features of ladon beam were a satisfactory",
                " energy resolution (up to about 10%  fwhm, at maximum",
                " energy), an  extremely low bremsstrahlung background",
                " (about 5% integrated over the whole spectrum above 2",
                " MeV),  an intensity of about 10**5 photons/s, and an",
                " almost complete linear polarization."
              ]
            }
          ],
